cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use OAcquire in your research, please cite the paper (preferred-citation), not this software record."
title: "OAcquire: A Multi-Source Corpus Acquisition Layer for Agentic Systematic Reviews"
abstract: >-
  OAcquire resolves bibliographic identifiers (DOI, PMID, PMCID) to legally
  retrievable open-access full texts by cascading across seven independent
  sources, validating each candidate document, and emitting an auditable
  retrieval log suitable for PRISMA-compliant reporting. It exposes a typed
  single-call interface for LLM agents and automated pipelines, a batch CLI,
  and a browser-based interface for non-technical researchers.
type: software
version: 2.0.0
date-released: 2026-07-12
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/pecesama/oacquire"
url: "https://oacquire.streamlit.app"
